1
00:00:00,083 --> 00:00:02,833
When I came, I didn’t think this was a prison

2
00:00:02,916 --> 00:00:05,166
I told myself they would ask me questions

3
00:00:05,583 --> 00:00:08,208
And when they’d finished, I would leave

4
00:00:08,791 --> 00:00:12,083
But I was surprised that after they’d asked me questions, they detained me

5
00:00:12,791 --> 00:00:15,041
Interviewer: Since you are from this area

6
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:17,041
What was this place before?

7
00:00:17,791 --> 00:00:18,916
This place used to be a church

8
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:21,666
Interviewer: Do you remember having come in here before?

9
00:00:21,666 --> 00:00:24,166
When the Christians were present here?

10
00:00:24,166 --> 00:00:26,666
Yes, I entered this place many times

11
00:00:26,666 --> 00:00:28,666
There was a cemetery there

12
00:00:29,666 --> 00:00:30,791
It had graves

13
00:00:30,916 --> 00:00:33,666
We came in here when we were young

14
00:00:34,041 --> 00:00:36,541
We used to come here in the 80s and 90s

15
00:00:37,083 --> 00:00:40,166
We came as families—us and the Christians

16
00:00:41,916 --> 00:00:45,625
Interviewer: Aside from being neighbors with the Christians in the area

17
00:00:45,916 --> 00:00:47,958
Did you have special relationships, like friendships, with Christians?

18
00:00:48,041 --> 00:00:52,791
Which made you come to this place?

19
00:00:52,916 --> 00:00:56,416
Yes, they know I have many relationships with Christians

20
00:00:56,791 --> 00:01:03,666
For that reason, I imagine they asked me who was a priest, and who was in this church

21
00:01:03,916 --> 00:01:08,208
And in the other church, and who lived in the archbishopric

22
00:01:09,791 --> 00:01:12,166
Interviewer: When they first brought you into this place

23
00:01:12,208 --> 00:01:17,333
Into this entrance—which is the entrance to the church or to the prison itself

24
00:01:17,833 --> 00:01:19,958
What was there at the beginning?

25
00:01:20,208 --> 00:01:21,458
How did they treat you?

26
00:01:21,500 --> 00:01:23,583
And how did they treat your belongings?

27
00:01:24,041 --> 00:01:26,791
Did they deal with you when they took information from you?

28
00:01:26,791 --> 00:01:28,333
How was it?

29
00:01:28,916 --> 00:01:30,625
They took information from me

30
00:01:30,791 --> 00:01:32,416
Interviewer: What information did they take from you?

31
00:01:33,916 --> 00:01:36,666
I told you, they asked me about people

32
00:01:37,333 --> 00:01:40,791
What do you know about the Christians who were in this area?

33
00:01:40,791 --> 00:01:43,208
Interviewer: Was this when you arrived?
Witness: Yes

34
00:01:43,333 --> 00:01:45,166
Interviewer: When they took your belongings

35
00:01:45,333 --> 00:01:47,541
Interviewer: Did they enter your name into the computer?
Witness: Yes

36
00:01:47,541 --> 00:01:48,791
Interviewer: Did they fill out a form?

37
00:01:48,833 --> 00:01:50,458
Yes, they took my personal information

38
00:01:51,541 --> 00:01:56,666
My full name, and what do you do? What is your job?

39
00:01:58,333 --> 00:02:01,541
What are your relations with people here in the area?

40
00:02:01,916 --> 00:02:03,541
Who do you know of the Christians?

41
00:02:04,708 --> 00:02:06,541
They asked me about all these things

42
00:02:06,916 --> 00:02:08,583
Interviewer: After they took your belongings

43
00:02:08,625 --> 00:02:09,625
Where did they take you?

44
00:02:10,583 --> 00:02:12,416
They took me and we entered the hall

45
00:02:13,916 --> 00:02:15,541
They interrogated me

46
00:02:16,916 --> 00:02:18,916
And that coincided with prayer time

47
00:02:19,416 --> 00:02:21,791
So I prayed two cycles as sunna

48
00:02:23,041 --> 00:02:24,333
After that I prayed the noon prayer

49
00:02:25,208 --> 00:02:27,333
In the archbishopric, then they took me back

50
00:02:28,041 --> 00:02:29,791
After they took me back they took me to the detention place

51
00:02:29,791 --> 00:02:30,791
To the prison upstairs

52
00:02:31,333 --> 00:02:33,166
I stayed upstairs for 28 days
